SOCCER SHOWCASE - BARCELONA AND ATLETICO IN THRILLING 3 - 3 DRAW . Barcelona and Atletico Madrid lived up to their no - holds - barred reputations on Saturday , sharing in a thrilling 3 - 3 draw in a top Spanish first division match at Nou Camp after the lead had changed hands three times . Champions Atletico went ahead after six minutes through Spain midfielder Jose Luis Caminero . But Barcelona hit back through striker Juan Pizzi and Luis Enrique Martinez to lead 2 - 1 at halftime . The visitors equalised on the hour thanks to Juan Vizcaino and then regained the lead from the penalty spot 13 minutes later through Argentine Juan Esnaider . But Brazilian Giovanni struck 12 minutes from time to earn Barcelona a point and ensure their unbeaten record this season remained intact . 
